!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

everyone /ˈɛvrɪˌwʌn/

1. PRON-INDEF You use everyone or everybody to refer to all the people in a particular group. (某群体中的) 所有人 

例： Everyone on the street was shocked when they heard the news. 听到这个消息，街上所有人都感到震惊。 

例： Not everyone thinks that the government is being particularly generous. 并不是所有人都认为政府是在特别慷慨。 

2. PRON-INDEF You use everyone or everybody to refer to all people. 人人 

例： Everyone wrestles with self-doubt and feels like a failure at times. 人人都会有与不自信作斗争、感觉自己是个失败者的时候。 

例： Everyone needs some free time for rest and relaxation. 人人都需要一些休息和放松的空闲时间。

</div>

